House Resolution 906
By: Representatives Henderson of the 113th, Lupton of the 83rd, and Gilliard of the 162nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Burnelle Henderson; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Burnelle Henderson was born on January 25, 1930, in Mecklenburg County,
3 Virginia, a beloved daughter of Jack and Jugurtha Carrington; and
4 WHEREAS, Burnelle Henderson was educated in the Mecklenburg School System and
5 graduated from West End High School on June 7, 1949, becoming the first and only among
6 her siblings to complete high school; and
7 WHEREAS, after receiving her nursing certificate, she cared for the elderly and babies in
8 Virginia and Washington, D.C., area hospitals before working at the Western Electric
9 Telephone Company in Arlington, retiring at the age of 55; and
10 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Burnelle Henderson was a devoted member
11 of Cedar Grove, faithfully supporting the church with her tithes for over 50 years regardless
12 of the distance or other congregations she attended; and
